{"questionId":"9482","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question asks you to investigate some properties of the sequence of functions of the&nbsp;form <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{f_n}(x) = {\\text{cos}}\\left( {n\\,{\\text{arccos}}\\,x} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>arccos</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, −1 ≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> ≤ 1 and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n \\in {\\mathbb{Z}^ + }\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><strong>Important:</strong> When sketching graphs in this question, you are <strong>not</strong> required to find the&nbsp;coordinates of any axes intercepts or the coordinates of any stationary points unless requested.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>On a new set of axes, sketch the graphs of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = {f_2}(x)\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>f</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = {f_4}(x)\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>f</mi> <mn>4</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </math></span> for −1 ≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span> ≤ 1.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = {f_2}(x)\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>f</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = {f_4}(x)\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>f</mi> <mn>4</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/92680e22bce2217d1af72b4066aa59d71182280e.png\"></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9482","referenceCode":"SPM.3.AHL.TZ0.2c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"On a new set of axes, sketch the graphs of y = f 2 ( x ) and y = f 4 ( x ) for −1 ≤ x ≤ 1.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.9—Reciprocal trig ratios and their pythagorean identities. Inverse circular functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}